725655f-a.text:
79th Street east side, between Thirty-first and Thirty-second Avenues. This house when Trains Meadow Road was in existent was at the N.E. corner of the last mentioned Road and 79th Street. The house formerly of frame was owned by J. Peterson in 1873 and Mrs. Obell in 1896.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

725656f-a.text:
79th Street, east side, between 32nd and 31st Avenues, showing the old Barclay Farmhouse (1852-1860) and outhouses. It was owned by J. Johnson, Barclay’s son-in-law, in 1873. The house and land were formerly situated on the west side of Trains Meadow Road, before the thoroughfare was discontinued and the area developed into a residential neighborhood.

March, 1924

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
